====Guest speaker at Hogwarts====
[[File:Rita Skeeter's Great Hall speech HM.png|250px|thumb|right|Rita Skeeter giving a speech to the students of Hogwarts in the [[Great Hall]]]]
Rita was a guest speaker at [[Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry]] during the [[1986–1987 school year]]. Prior to the reveal, the identity of the speaker generated quite a buzz throughout the school, with [[Rowan Khanna]]'s guess being an [[Auror]], the [[Minister for Magic]], or a random [[Arithmancer]], while [[Jacob's sibling]] thought it to perhaps be [[Patricia Rakepick|the person]] [[Albus Dumbledore]] had been searching for throughout the school year. [[Professor]] [[Minerva McGonagall]] introduced her to the school in the [[Great Hall]], with Rita adding a bit more detail, stating herself to be "a widely popular writer for the ''[[Daily Prophet]]''".<ref name="HM3WWF"/>

She then gave a speech about the general [[wizarding world]] being curious about the happenings within Hogwarts, as, [[Cursed Vaults]] aside, there apparently were talks about Hogwarts having the most promising assemblage of students in years, and that, in order to find out who the brightest student was, Professor Dumbledore had given the ''Prophet'' permission to observe and conduct a friendly competition, with the winner featuring on a front page article in the ''Prophet'' to start. Rita then observed [[Potions (class)|Potions]], [[Transfiguration (class)|Transfiguration]], [[Flying (class)|Flying]], and [[Charms (class)|Charms]] classes, much to most of the instructors' annoyance, before eventually forcing Jacob's sibling, who suspected that Rita knew something about the whereabouts of their [[Jacob (Hogwarts expellee)|missing brother]], to decide the winner of the competition.<ref name="HM3WWF">{{HM|3|Wizarding World Famous}}</ref>

====Book researcher====
[[File:Rita Skeeter speaking to Jacob's sibling HM.png|250px|thumb|left|Rita speaking with Jacob's sibling]]
Subsequent to her guest speaker role, during the [[1987–1988 school year]], Rita returned to Hogwarts to interview the staff as research for a book she was writing. She was particularly interested in uncovering Hogwarts's dark and dangerous secrets in the hopes her book would force the [[headmaster]], who she had a dislike for, to step down. Jacob's sibling was assigned as a chaperone while she interviewed [[Rubeus Hagrid]], [[Torvus]] the [[centaur]], and Professor [[Silvanus Kettleburn]] and inspected the [[Restricted Section]] of the [[Hogwarts Library]].<ref name="HM4RR"/>

Jacob's sibling reported her questions and motivations to Albus Dumbledore, who revealed to them that Rita was an unregistered Animagus who was using her abilities to eavesdrop at the time. Dumbledore convinced her to return to human form and they all came to an agreement to not expose Rita's abilities in exchange for her not publishing her book critical of Hogwarts.<ref name="HM4RR">{{HM|4|Rita Returns}}</ref>

====Denouncing Hogsmeade====
During the same school year, Rita scathingly reviewed the village of [[Hogsmeade]], saving most of her venom for [[Zonko's Joke Shop]], causing the village to lose business revenue and Bilmes to temporarily shut down Zonko's. When confronted by Bilmes and Jacob's sibling, she revealed it was due to her grudge against Bilmes for preventing her from joining the Slug Club. Bilmes got revenge on Skeeter by allowing her to drink a mug of [[Butterbeer]] containing [[Belch Powder]], much to Skeeter's further anger.<ref name="HM4SZ"/>

====Harassing Celestina Warbeck====
Skeeter travelled to Hogwarts again in the [[1988–1989 school year]] to interview the famous singer [[Celestina Warbeck]] about why she had returned to Hogwarts. Skeeter was present on the [[Hogsmeade station]] platform when Warbeck arrived. Warbeck disguised herself with a feather boa and Jacob's sibling escorted her away from the scene before Skeeter could spot her.<ref name="HM5CNG"/>

[[File:Rita Skeeter being scared away with frogs HM.png|250px|thumb|right|Rita Skeeter opening a cupboard full of frogs]]
Skeeter later harassed Warbeck for information about why she was at Hogwarts in her dressing room on the [[Hogwarts Quidditch pitch]], which she refused to divulge to her, so Skeeter told her she would instead have to fabricate quotes by simply reading her face. Jacob's sibling and [[Tulip Karasu]] thought that, in order to get rid of her so they could [[Anapneo|unblock]] Warbeck's blocked throat, they would spook her with [[frog]]s spawned with [[Frog Spawn Soap]], as Tulip heard frogs made her uneasy. Jacob's sibling told her a student was trapped in a locker, which Rita believed, thinking it would make a good story, and she opened it, being showered with frogs, causing her to flee in horror.<ref name="HM5CNG">{{HM|5|CELESTINA's NEW GROOVE}}</ref>

====International Confederation of Wizard's Conference====
Rita covered the [[International Confederation of Wizards' Conference]] during the summer of [[1994]], describing [[Albus Dumbledore]] as an "obsolete dingbat".<ref name="GOF18">{{GOF|B|18}}</ref>

====1994 Quidditch World Cup====
