In the same school year, following the employment and sacking of Professor [[Elspeth MacGillony]], Skeeter wrote about the incident and voiced her concern of the continued employment of controversial teachers, claiming that it was not unlike when [[Albus Dumbledore]] was Headmaster.<ref name="MacGillony">{{MA}} {{See image 2|File:Rita Skeeter's report about Elspeth MacGillony 1 MA.jpg|File:Rita Skeeter's report about Elspeth MacGillony 2 MA.jpg}}</ref>

In [[April]] [[2014]], just before the opening matches of the [[2014 Quidditch World Cup|427th Quidditch World Cup]], [[Brazil|Brazilian]] manager [[José Barboza]] called the [[Wales|Welsh]] [[Chaser]]s "''talentless [[hag]]s''" over drinks with Rita Skeeter. These remarks became public, and Welsh manager [[Gwenog Jones]] promptly threatened to "''[[curse]]'' [his] ''face off''".<ref name="bra-v-wal">{{PM}} - [[BRAZIL VERSUS WALES]] (Archived)</ref><ref name="PM-QWC">{{PM}} - [[Quidditch World Cup 1990 - 2014]] (Archived)</ref> This created great tension between Jones and Barboza, culminating in a brawl between the two following the [[Brazilian National Quidditch team|Brazil]] vs. [[Welsh National Quidditch team|Wales]] match of the quarter-finals on [[4 June]]. Gwenog Jones attempted to keep her promise to curse off Barboza's face in full view of the packed stadium. The Welsh manager was dragged from the pitch by her own [[Beater]]s, and was later put in custody, and the ''[[Daily Prophet]]'' later reported that [[Healer]]s confirmed Barboza's skin had almost regrown.<ref name="bra-v-wal"/>

[[File:Rita quill.jpg|200px|thumb|right|Rita standing with her infamous acid green quill]]
Rita Skeeter wrote a gossip column in ''The Daily Prophet'' about the Quidditch World Cup on [[8 July]], [[2014]], in which she mentioned that she was about to publish a new book about [[Dumbledore's Army]] on [[31 July]] called ''[[Dumbledore's Army: The Dark Side of the Demob]]''.

